The paper deals with channel estimation and beamforming in massive MIMO systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel receiver architecture and discusses the benefits of using the proposed technique during the initial access phase, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the use of analog beamforming, which is a key aspect of Massive MIMO systems and falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel technique for channel estimation, which falls under the sub-category of Architecture (cs.AR).
